"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-27-tom-daley-knitting-fans-declare-olympics-started-21309599\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"When is notTom Daleyknitting?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 29, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Team GB diver was at it again todaywith his yarn and needlesas he took aprime poolside spotfor the2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 31, \"to\": 153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 138, \"end\": 152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom, 30 - whobecamesomewhat of a meme for his knitting habitsat the last TokyoOlympicsin 2021 - just could not get enough of the woollen hobby as he hunched over a jumper while supporting Yasmin Harper and Scarlett Mew at the Aquatics Centre.\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 361, \"end\": 369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_O'Hara\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.645717299327181e-14, \"text\": \"Scarlett\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_O'Hara\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_O'Hara\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two athletes won the first Team GB medals of Paris with their dives in the Women's Synchronized 3m Springboard this morning after a dramatic opening ceremony last night featuring performances fromCeline DionandLady Gaga.\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999998257340091, \"rank\": 1.7426590657715132e-07, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 448, \"end\": 453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2014254851475654e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.04509000436429e-27, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athlete, who took up knitting during the Covid-19 lockdown in March 2020, worked on a blue, white and red jumper with his surname emblazoned on the back.\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 782, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom, who previously said he finds knitting a cathartic distraction between events, won gold in the men's 10m synchronised high board event at Tokyo, where he was regularly photographed in the act.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999993943467431, \"rank\": 6.053926371724875e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having published a practical guide to knitting called Made With Love in October 2022, he's somewhat of an expert after just a few years wielding his needle.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans were loving the pictures of Tom enjoying himself, and @ClaireD143 wrote on X: 'The Olympics only officially starts when Tom Daley gets his knitting out.'\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1265, \"end\": 1274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8930036641203e-56, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Tom Daley sitting watching the diving with his knitting is the cutest thing in the world,' added @brooksybradshaw.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1301, \"end\": 1310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8930036641203e-56, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It would not be an Olympics without Tom Daley knitting in the crowd,' commented @hyyh_m19.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8930036641203e-56, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom will begin his Olympic efforts on\\u00a0Monday 29 July, competing in the 10m synchronised platform event.\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He looked to be relaxed on the first day of sport, having been team GB's flagbearer along with rower Helen Glover during the drenched opening ceremony on Friday.\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1678, \"end\": 1685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999998257340091, \"rank\": 1.7426590657715132e-07, \"text\": \"team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tbrowser thatsupports HTML5 \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tvideo  Up Next  As Team GB took part in the parade of athletes along the River Seine on a boat, he and Glover recreated the famous Titanic film scene where Leonardo DiCaprio holds Kate Winslet on the bow of the doomed ship.\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 2120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.883995053068471e-13, \"text\": \"JavaScript\", \"types\": [\"Q9143\", \"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\"}, {\"begin\": 1883, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"score\": 0.9999999999545253, \"rank\": 4.5316921554931993e-11, \"text\": \"HTML5\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\"}, {\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999998257340091, \"rank\": 1.7426590657715132e-07, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1970, \"end\": 1981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"score\": 0.9999999823103282, \"rank\": 1.76331200826655e-08, \"text\": \"Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Glover\"}, {\"begin\": 2053, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_DiCaprio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leonardo DiCaprio\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_DiCaprio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_DiCaprio\"}, {\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Winslet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Winslet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Winslet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Winslet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Celine Dion, who sang the theme My Heart Will Go On for the Oscar-winning movie, closed the ceremony with a moving performance from the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.619019980086042e-45, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Singing Edith Piaf's L'Hymne A L'Amour, it was the Canadian singer's live performance since revealing she has the rare neurological condition, stiff person syndrome (SPS), which causes muscle spasms and progressive muscular inflexibility.\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2324, \"end\": 2332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999993579938078, \"rank\": 3.8570960881222295e-07, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 2439, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Super_Proton_Synchrotron\", \"score\": 0.9447284569906